      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Kilnaga wrote:</div><div class="orig">No. <br /> <br />Get to know other crafters, the game isn't meant to be solo'd. I get my off class materials from the other crafters in my linksell. Learn to network with the other crafters around you and help each other out.</div></div> <br /> <br />Actually, it can be done solo.  It's just that the more focused you want to be in a particular area, the more help you're going to have to call in in order to be successful. <br /> <br />For armorer, if you're wanting to make things like bronze or sentinel's chainmail you're either going to need to rank up Weaver or you're going to have to source your tabards from someone else.  There's no getting around it, and it's not going to change.  When you move up into bronze haubergeons, the cloth requirement is much less (one bolt of cotton cloth instead of a finished piece of cloth armor).  When you jump up to iron haubergeons, it still remains about the same only the cloth and leather components go up one tier. <br /> <br />Unless your reasoning behind not using the market wards is because you're playing on a dated PC that struggles to load all the models, there is no &quot;can't&quot; in your problem.  There is a lot of &quot;I choose not to&quot; and there's a difference.  You choosing not to do those things necessary in order to accomplish your goals is not the same as the goals being impossible to accomplish. <br /> <br />You're not going to be able to take a straight line path to where you want to go unless you involve other people.  If you're willing to take the time to develop a rounded character, there's very little you can't do solo.  It's a choice you're going to have to make, but the process will start with you eliminating the &quot;I can't&quot; excuse.</div>
